detailedDescription.articleBody: Subway is an American fast food restaurant franchise that primarily sells submarine sandwiches, salads and beverages. It was founded by Fred DeLuca and Peter Buck in 1965 and has expanded to become a global franchise.

detailedDescription.articleBody: The doctor of nursing practice is a degree in nursing. In the United States, the DNP is one of two doctorate degrees in nursing, the other being the PhD.

detailedDescription.articleBody: The Doctor of Health Science is a post-professional academic doctoral degree for those who intend to pursue or advance a professional practice career in Health Sciences and Health Care Delivery Systems, which can include clinical practice, education, administration, and research.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Amref Health Africa was founded in 1957 by three surgeons as the Flying Doctors of East Africa. Three doctors – Sir Michael Wood, Sir Archibald McIndoe and Tom Rees – drew up a plan to provide medical care in East Africa, where they had all worked for many years as reconstructive surgeons.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: Amref Health Africa की स्थापना 1957 में तीन सर्जनों द्वारा पूर्वी अफ्रीका के फ्लाइंग डॉक्टर्स के रूप में की गई थी, तीन डॉक्टरों - सर माइकल वुड, सर आर्चीबाल्ड मैकिंडो और टॉम रीस - ने पूर्वी अफ्रीका में चिकित्सा देखभाल प्रदान करने की योजना तैयार की, जहाँ उन्होंने सभी के लिए काम किया था।
